1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,460
Hey everybody, welcome to this A2 English listening practice video.

2
00:00:05,460 --> 00:00:10,780
You can use this video to train your listening and comprehension as I speak.

3
00:00:10,780 --> 00:00:12,100
You ready?

4
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:15,940
So today I'm going to talk about travel.

5
00:00:15,940 --> 00:00:18,340
Traveling is one of the funnest activities.

6
00:00:18,340 --> 00:00:20,420
I've always loved traveling.

7
00:00:20,420 --> 00:00:25,260
When I was young, my family and I traveled to Hawaii many times.

8
00:00:25,260 --> 00:00:31,052
In case you don't know much about Hawaii, it's an island in the middle of the Pacific Ocean

9
00:00:31,052 --> 00:00:34,580
and it's also one of the 50 states of the US.

10
00:00:34,580 --> 00:00:37,580
I've been there about six or seven times.

11
00:00:37,580 --> 00:00:40,300
I don't remember how many exactly.

12
00:00:40,300 --> 00:00:43,550
It's definitely one of my favorite places in the world.

13
00:00:43,550 --> 00:00:50,340
Hawaii has plenty of really beautiful beaches and the lifestyle there is slow and calm.

14
00:00:50,340 --> 00:00:54,576
But even though Hawaii is one of my favorite places to travel to,

15
00:00:54,576 --> 00:01:01,220
in general I prefer the countryside, the forest, or the mountains more than the beach.

16
00:01:01,220 --> 00:01:05,180
So I love taking camping trips and road trips.

17
00:01:05,180 --> 00:01:09,039
I've taken a few different road trips through the US before

18
00:01:09,039 --> 00:01:14,060
and I just recently took a road trip through the Tuscany region of Italy.

19
00:01:14,060 --> 00:01:18,100
It was one of the most incredible experiences I've ever had.

20
00:01:18,100 --> 00:01:20,500
If you ever get the chance to go to Italy,

21
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:25,020
I highly recommend you to rent a car and drive through Tuscany.

22
00:01:25,020 --> 00:01:27,780
Trust me, you won't be disappointed.

23
00:01:27,780 --> 00:01:33,876
Speaking of Europe, I also took a backpacking trip through Portugal in Spain a few years ago.

24
00:01:33,876 --> 00:01:37,660
It was my first time backpacking and it wasn't easy.

25
00:01:37,660 --> 00:01:42,032
We spent a lot of time walking and taking buses and trains

26
00:01:42,032 --> 00:01:46,060
and the whole time we had these big backpacks on our backs.

27
00:01:46,060 --> 00:01:52,180
We stayed in some pretty low quality hostels and thus we had some bad experiences.

28
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:57,580
The worst thing that happened to me was that I was bitten by bedbugs when I was in Madrid.

29
00:01:57,580 --> 00:02:03,500
I don't know if you've ever been bitten by bedbugs before but it's not a fun experience.

30
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:07,900
And for me it was worse because I have really sensitive skin.

31
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:11,620
So I didn't just have little red spots on my skin.

32
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:16,220
I had big swollen sores all over my arms.

33
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:19,305
So if you plan on staying in hostels when you travel,

34
00:02:19,305 --> 00:02:23,140
you should definitely read the online reviews first.

35
00:02:23,140 --> 00:02:28,420
Sometimes it's better to pay a little more money to stay in a better place.

36
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:34,540
Some people only like staying in hotels and other people really like Airbnb's.

37
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:39,780
And lately I've been staying at Airbnb's no matter where I travel.

38
00:02:39,780 --> 00:02:44,020
It's definitely better than staying in hostels in my opinion.

39
00:02:44,020 --> 00:02:48,020
Another aspect of travel that's really important is the flight.

40
00:02:48,020 --> 00:02:51,580
This is probably the worst part about traveling.

41
00:02:51,580 --> 00:02:54,060
Actually it is the worst part, definitely.

42
00:02:54,060 --> 00:02:58,700
I've been pretty lucky because I haven't had any really bad flights 

43
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:06,020
but I have had experiences with long delays and cancelled flights which can really ruin your trip.

44
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:11,140
There were two times when I had to spend the night at the airport which was terrible.

45
00:03:11,140 --> 00:03:14,660
I hope you guys don't ever have that experience.

46
00:03:14,660 --> 00:03:18,800
So overall there are good and bad things about traveling

47
00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:23,260
but I think we can all agree that it's nice to travel once in a while.

48
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:25,580
Okay that's all for today.

49
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:29,500
Leave a comment and tell me your favorite place that you've traveled to.

50
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,960
I'll see you in next video.
